Electrical Engineer Job (Electrical Manufacturing), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting for a multinational company that has been active in the electrical manufacturing sector. Our client is seeking a professional with a background in electrical engineering for the job of Electrical Engineer, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. Our client has become a worldwide leader in their industry segment and delivers value to its clients by betting on constant business development, excellence and high-quality human resources. The winning candidate will experience a dynamic, stimulating and international environment, allowing them to grow professionally. The company offers good prospects for career progression Key job responsibilities will include: To help in analysis and interpretation of bid documentsBe in charge of electrical project managementBe in charge of cost estimations in proposals, technical offers and specificationsMaintain relationships with customers and suppliers Requirements: Electrical engineering degreeTwo to 3 years’ experience in electrical projectsStrong networking in government/private companiesCost estimationExcellent team work and organizational skillsExcellent English communication skills, both written and verbal All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to Industrial@monroeconsulting.com
